                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d496">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.113/246: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Child</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-04-13T03:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 13, 1922—3 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 11:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>56. Department’s instruction of March 4, 1 p.m. number 23. Italian Government
                    informs Embassy it has arranged that no sales of Italian arms and ammunition
                    shall take place in China either to Chinese buyers or to their agents of
                    whatsoever nationality. Text of note by next pouch.<note n="63"
                        xml:id="d496fn63">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Child</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
